  <td valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="contentarea"><P align=center><STRONG>It's getting closer!<BR>104&nbsp;days to the 2009 Spec-Savers Ironman 70.3 South Africa <BR>and&nbsp;181 to Ironman South Africa</STRONG></P></td>
  </tr>

 <tr> 
  	<td valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subcontentarea">
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#D4262F" style="margin-bottom:15px;">
  <tr> <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subarticleheading">2008 FORD  IRONMAN WORLD CHAMPIONSHIPS IN KONA</td></tr>
  <tr><td valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subarticlearea">
<table width="202" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#D4262F" class="picturetable">
<tr><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><a href = "http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news//open_big_news.asp?showcase=Kona Flower.jpg" target="_blank"><img name="pic" border="0" src="http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news/sml_Kona Flower.jpg" style="background-color: #CCCCCC"></td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><a href = "http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news//open_big_news.asp?showcase=IM_KonaLogo.jpg" target="_blank"><img name="pic" border="0" src="http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news/sml_IM_KonaLogo.jpg" style="background-color: #CCCCCC"></td></tr>
</table>
<P>Yes it's that time of year again. The Ironman of all Ironman races in Kona - the World Championships! On Saturday,&nbsp;11 October all eyes will be on the 1800 triathletes as they battle it out in the scorching heat in Hawaii. </P>
<P>As Race Director Diana Bertsch says, "If you are a triathlete, there is no bigger day in this sport than the Ford Ironman World Championship. It is the race that defined our sport as it came of age and continues to be the defining race in our sport for any avid triathlete."</P>
<P>If you are lucky enough to be on the starting line you would have either won your place in the lottery or qualified at one of the qualifying events held around the world - either way you are in for the time of your life!&nbsp;</P>
<P>You can log onto Ironman.com for live updates and track an athlete on Saturday,&nbsp;11 October 2008. Don't miss any of the action as the 2008 Ford World Ironman Champion is crowned.<BR><BR>To all the South African athletes making their way to Kona we wish you all the best.</P>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
 <tr> 
  	<td valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subcontentarea">
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#D4262F" style="margin-bottom:15px;">
  <tr> <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subarticleheading">NEW RUN COURSE FOR 2009 IRONMAN 70.3 SOUTH AFRICA</td></tr>
  <tr><td valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="subarticlearea">
<table width="202" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#D4262F" class="picturetable">
<tr><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><a href = "http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news//open_big_news.asp?showcase=IMBC2008_BestOf_ (126).JPG" target="_blank"><img name="pic" border="0" src="http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news/sml_IMBC2008_BestOf_ (126).JPG" style="background-color: #CCCCCC"></td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><a href = "http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news//open_big_news.asp?showcase=IMBC_logo(3).jpg" target="_blank"><img name="pic" border="0" src="http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/images/news/sml_IMBC_logo(3).jpg" style="background-color: #CCCCCC"></td></tr>
</table>
<P><B></B></P>
<P>To make the run course of the 2009 Spec-Savers Ironman 70.3 South Africa&nbsp;more spectator friendly, and to assist you the athletes, the course has been adjusted. We ask that you please familiarise yourself with this change to ensure that your race runs as smoothly as possible.</P>
<P>In short athletes will leave the Transition Area after the cycle and run down passed the Orient Theatre, be redirected along side the Finish Line shutte and out onto the Esplanade, continue along the Eastern Esplanade, up into John Bailie Road towards the Schenker Turn-Around Aids Station. Please note that you will no longer complete the Bunkers Hill loop. On your return, and before starting your second loop, you will once again run along side the Finish Line but this time you will move out onto the Pier before turning around and completing the second loop. </P>
<P>There are a total of&nbsp;three Aids Stations on the run (approximately 2km apart) and you will complete&nbsp;three loops before finally making your way to the Finish Line.</P>
<P>We trust that this change will allow you to be encouraged more by the spectators and improve your race. </P>
    <a href="http://newsletters.onlineinnovations.com/ironman/newsletter.asp?NewsletterID=8419&ArticleID=8419">Click here to view the new run course map</a>
</td>
</tr>
